Our previous work has shown that SIRS simulations perform optimally when 15–50% of a model population of 100,000 is infected over the course of a modeled epidemic. Therefore, scaling values, γ, for each country were determined by first calculating the range of scaling values yielding a total attack rate between 15% and 50% for each season, i, ([γ15, i, γ 50, i]), then choosing a single country-specific scaling value based on the following rule:




γ={if∃γ∈ℝ:γ15,i<γ<γ50,i∀i:maxi=1n(γ15,i)else:mini=1n(γ50,i)}


